      "comment": "FEAR THE DRAGON (1) brought up his 30th career win last start at Murray Bridge Straight (17.21). Speedy beginner who should be in the action early off the inside. Well placed and can measure up. STARLIGHT RIOT (4) made light work of a wide draw last time with a slick early sectional but gathered in and had to settle for the minors, finishing second (19.60) at Angle Park over 342m. Form from her last run is proving very strong. Overdue and is among the main hopes. STIFLER (5) won again in an impressive display after running them ragged to make it two on the bounce, scoring by half a length (16.73) at this track over 300m. Ran the fastest time on the program in his latest win. One of the prime contenders. FLYING HUGO (8) has strong credentials over this journey.",
